        name "File integrity"
        check_description "A process shall be employed to provide an integrity verification mechanism for
            +b all scripts, executables and other important files included in a product."
        requirement_id "SM-6"
        title "File Integrity"
        description "This requirement focuses on ensuring the integrity of files within an
            +b industrial control system (ICS). It mandates the implementation of mechanisms
            +b to detect unauthorized changes to files, thereby protecting the system from
            +b potential tampering and maintaining its reliability and security."
        [ key_aspects
            {
                aspect "Detection Mechanisms"
                details "Implement tools and processes that can monitor and detect unauthorized changes
                    +b to critical files, including executable files, configuration files, and data
                    +b files."
            {
                aspect "Integrity Verification"
                details "Utilize cryptographic hashes or checksums to verify the integrity of files.
                    +b Regularly compare current file states with known good baselines to identify
                    +b discrepancies."
            {
                aspect "Response Procedures"
                details "Establish and document procedures to respond to integrity breaches. This
                    +b includes identifying the scope of the breach, mitigating potential damage, and
                    +b restoring affected files to their original state."
            {
                aspect "Configuration Management"
                details "Ensure that changes to file configurations are tracked and authorized. Maintain
                    +b a log of changes to support audit and forensic activities."
