            "Supplier Evaluation: Conduct thorough evaluations of suppliers to ensure they can meet the defined security requirements. This includes assessing their security capabilities and their ability to address potential vulnerabilities."
            "Contractual Obligations: Ensure that security requirements are included in contracts with suppliers. This establishes a formal obligation for suppliers to adhere to the specified security criteria."
            "Verification and Validation: Implement processes to verify and validate that external components meet the security requirements. This may involve testing, audits, or certifications."
